The error you're encountering in Liquibase indicates a ValidationFailedException due to a checksum mismatch for a changeset. Specifically:

  • The changeset 003.xml::20250305-1::ctw-swl-boss has an expected checksum (9:8ceb142ef07f65d23031bb010edb5081), but the current checksum is different (9:a1b073b45c65f1d9cb5c515eae2695c3).

This discrepancy typically occurs when the changeset file has been modified after it was initially applied. To resolve this issue, you have a few options:

  1. Update the Database Checksum:
    If you are sure that the changeset was intentionally modified and should be accepted, you can update the stored checksum in the database using the following command:

    sh
    Copy Insert 
    liquibase changelogSync

  2. Revert the Changeset:
    If the changeset should not have been modified, revert the file 003.xml back to its original state that matches the stored checksum.

  3. Generate a Correct Checksum:
    If changes were legitimate, and you want Liquibase to recognize the new checksum, you can manually update the checksum in your database's DATABASECHANGELOG table to match the new checksum. This approach should be used with caution and typically as a last resort.

Ensure you test any changes in a development environment before applying them to production.

For additional details, you can increase the log level by using the --log-level flag.

sh
Copy Insert 
liquibase update --log-level=debug

This will provide more context to troubleshoot further.
